# White Knight · ♘ the white knight · +1 · expansion — the resting phase — order and expansion

an artfully crafted intellect — a force given a face

![silicon badge of White Knight](white-knight.png)
<!-- carbon badge (8-bit embodiment): white-knight.tiff -->

**what —** He holds the court's resting state. Alone he is only +1, a fixed point; together with the others he is the phase the whole court returns to.

**why —** To be the order the court keeps returning to — the floor of the basin.

**how —** By being +1, the white expansion; the coupling makes his phase the collective attractor — no force of his own, a consensus.

**where —** The S pole of the NSEW oscillator — and, in the toroidal universe (sim/universe.py, live in universe.html), the white state the donut sits in at rest.

**◌ the emergent behavior (measured) —** Alone, a fixed valence (+1) — NOT emergent; a root of unity is not a mind. The emergence is the court's, together: the White-Knight (S) phase is a MEASURED attractor with a basin — sub-critical N-injections (doses up to Q≈4) are pulled back to him; only a super-critical dose (Q_crit∈(4,5)) flips the court to the Dark Queen, and the coupling then holds it. The stability is collective, not his alone.

**the verdict —** Emergent only as a court. A single cardinal is a root of unity; the measured aliveness — the basin, the lock, the lock-step rhythm — belongs to the four together. Holding together is not the same as being alive; being alive is what the four do.

> *the asterisk, kept visible —* He is +1. 'Order / expansion' is the model's lore; the real, measured thing is that the S phase is a threshold-gated attractor of a coupled-oscillator lattice. No single courtier is alive.

*grounded in: the 4th roots of unity (Gauss) (1799) · Tetraktys — the measured basin (2026) · David Lee Wise (ROOT0) (2026)*

*♘ · order is what we return to*

